{% doc %}
  Virtual Compare — a full-page experience that places a set of products
  on the shopper from one uploaded photo, then lets them add to cart or open a
  product.

  This file is the SSR body only. The platform-generated wrapper supplies the
  outer container `<div>` (the visibility gate, the `data-spectrum-*`
  attributes). Unlike the PDP try-on snippet, this snippet is PAGE-scoped and
  has no `product` global: the products to try on come from the page URL query
  (`?products=<handle>,<handle>,…`) and are fetched client-side via
  `Spectrum.products.getByHandle`. The body therefore SSRs only the masthead
  (for LCP), an empty mount root, and a JSON props block; the JS asset builds
  the whole flow (collection → photo → looks → mini-PDP) client-side.

  @param {string} mutation_handle - Mutation handle for DOM scoping (infrastructure).
  @param {string} experience_handle - Experience handle for attribution (infrastructure).
  @param {object} variant - Resolved snippet-instance variant; merchant-edited
                            props live on `variant.content`.
  @param {object} mo - spectrum_snippet_instance metaobject drop.

  variant.content fields (presentation only):
    - eyebrow                  {string}  small label above the heading
    - heading                  {string}  studio headline
    - subheading               {string}  optional line above the product grid on the first screen (blank → hidden)
    - cta_text                 {string}  start-button label
    - fallback_collection      {string}  collection handle shown when the URL has no products (blank → featured)
    - daily_generation_limit   {number}  per-shopper daily generation cap
    - consent_text             {string}  consent copy — the dedicated consent step body, and (when inline_consent is on) the fine print under the product-list consent checkbox; carries the biometric (face) data disclosure and the third-party AI processor; the engineering default needs legal sign-off before live biometric collection
    - inline_consent           {boolean} default on — drop the dedicated consent step and gate the product-list start button on a single inline consent checkbox; set false for the dedicated consent step; consent record is unchanged
    - step1_heading            {string}  heading on the consent step (blank → platform default; unused when inline_consent is on)
    - step2_heading            {string}  heading on the add-a-photo step (blank → platform default)
    - step2_subheading         {string}  guidance under the add-a-photo heading (blank → platform default)
    - step2_confirm_heading    {string}  title beside the uploaded photo once ready (blank → platform default)
    - step2_confirm_subheading {string}  note beside the uploaded photo once ready (blank → platform default)
    - step3_heading            {string}  heading template on the results step; {count} → look count (blank → automatic singular/plural default)
    - step3_subheading         {string}  optional line under the results heading (blank → hidden)
    - show_branding            {boolean} show the Spectrum watermark on the result images (internal)

  @example
  {% render '_sai-snippet-b309s2jg',
    variant: variant,
    mo: mo,
    mutation_handle: 'mut-b309s2jgabcd1234',
    experience_handle: 'try-on-studio'
  %}
{% enddoc %}

{%- comment -%}
  Page-scoped: the products are NOT known at render time — they live in the URL
  query string and are resolved client-side. So there is no product SSR here and
  no product-conditional gate; the snippet always renders its shell, and the JS
  reads `?products=` (falling back to the merchant's `fallback_collection`, then
  the store's featured products).

  JSON data block contract: every interpolated value is piped through `| json`.
  `| json` unicode-escapes `<`, `>`, and line separators, so merchant-authored
  strings (consent copy, headings) cannot terminate the surrounding <script>
  element. Never `| escape` inside a JSON <script> block — HTML entities are not
  decoded inside <script> raw-text, which breaks the client-side JSON.parse.
{%- endcomment -%}

{% stylesheet %}
/* Virtual Compare (b309s2jg) — full-page multi-product try-on.
   Every colour/typography value derives from the merchant's --sai-* theme
   tokens; the design role-colours below map the editorial studio look onto
   whatever palette the storefront ships, so the studio reads native on any
   theme rather than carrying a hardcoded palette. */

.sai-b309s2jg {
  /* Re-base every surface onto the brand cream (#F4F1EA), matching the virtual
     try-on studio, instead of the theme's white --sai-color-bg; the plate/
     surface tokens below derive from this token. */
  --sai-color-bg: #F4F1EA;
  /* Design role-colours mapped onto theme tokens (ink ramp + accent + stage). */
  --v-ink: var(--sai-color-fg);
  --v-ink-2: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 64%, transparent);
  --v-ink-3: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 42%, transparent);
  --v-line: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 14%, transparent);
  --v-line-2: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 8%, transparent);
  --v-plate: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 6%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  --v-accent: var(--sai-color-primary);
  --v-accent-fg: var(--sai-color-primary-fg);
  --v-accent-soft: color-mix(in srgb, var(--v-accent) 12%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  --v-on-stage: #ffffff;
  --v-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 4%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  /* Success (Photo ready): prefer the theme token, fall back to a fixed green so
     the badge never renders colourless on themes without --sai-color-success. */
  --v-success: var(--sai-color-success, rgb(31 138 77));
  --v-success-soft: color-mix(in srgb, var(--v-success) 14%, var(--sai-color-bg));

  display: block;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  inline-size: 100%;
  min-block-size: 60vh;
  padding-block: var(--sai-size-6);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--v-ink);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-body);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-body-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight);
}

.sai-b309s2jg *,
.sai-b309s2jg *::before,
.sai-b309s2jg *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Centered content column. */
.sai-b309s2jg__inner {
  inline-size: 100%;
  max-inline-size: 1120px;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

/* Eyebrow — the small uppercase label above each screen's own heading. */
.sai-b309s2jg__eyebrow {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-2);
  font-size: 0.6875rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.22em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
}

/* Mount root — the JS renders each screen (collection / photo / looks /
   mini-PDP) into this node. SSR shows a quiet loading state so the page is
   never blank before the asset boots (and a noscript fallback). */
.sai-b309s2jg__root {
  position: relative;
  min-block-size: 40vh;
}

/* Skeleton — the SSR placeholder shown until the JS renders the real collection
   (covers both the storefront-SDK wait and the product fetch). It mirrors the
   collection grid so the swap to real products is a seamless fade-in, not a
   spinner-then-jump. */
.sai-b309s2jg__skel-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: var(--sai-size-5) var(--sai-size-4);
}

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__skel-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 240px));
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--sai-size-6) var(--sai-size-5);
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__skel-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

/* Skeleton boxes each carry a non-breaking space in markup so themes that reset
   `div:empty { display: none }` (Dawn's base.css does) can't hide them. overflow is
   clipped so the filler space can't grow the box past its intended size. No explicit
   inline-size on the plate: the flex-column card's `align-items: stretch` sets the
   width and aspect-ratio derives the height. */
.sai-b309s2jg__skel-plate {
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  overflow: hidden;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__skel-line {
  block-size: 0.75em;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-2);
  overflow: hidden;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__skel-line--name {
  inline-size: 68%;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__skel-line--price {
  inline-size: 34%;
  block-size: 0.9em;
}

/* The shimmer — a highlight sweep across a plate-toned base. */
.sai-b309s2jg__skel-plate,
.sai-b309s2jg__skel-line {
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
  background-image: linear-gradient(
    100deg,
    transparent 30%,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-bg) 60%, transparent) 50%,
    transparent 70%
  );
  background-size: 220% 100%;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  animation: sai-b309s2jg-shimmer 1.4s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes sai-b309s2jg-shimmer {
  from {
    background-position: 180% 0;
  }
  to {
    background-position: -80% 0;
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__skel-plate,
  .sai-b309s2jg__skel-line {
    animation: none;
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__noscript {
  padding-block: var(--sai-size-6);
  text-align: center;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
}

/* Collection grid (first screen) — the products from the URL, an editorial
   multi-column grid that collapses to two-up on mobile. */
/* Mobile is a fixed two-up grid (a narrow viewport can't fit two auto-fit tracks
   at the card's preferred width, so auto-fit collapses to one column there). From
   the tablet breakpoint up, auto-fit + centered justification cluster any product
   count under the centered heading without an empty trailing column. */
.sai-b309s2jg__grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: var(--sai-size-5) var(--sai-size-4);
}

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 240px));
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--sai-size-6) var(--sai-size-5);
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__plate {
  position: relative;
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__plate-img {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__cname {
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-2);
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__cprice {
  margin-block-start: 0.125rem;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
}

/* Sticky start bar — the single "Try these on" CTA that opens the photo flow. */
.sai-b309s2jg__startbar {
  position: sticky;
  inset-block-end: var(--sai-size-3);
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-6);
}

/* Action buttons — primary (filled, theme accent) / ghost. */
.sai-b309s2jg__action {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  min-block-size: 3.25rem;
  padding: var(--sai-size-2) var(--sai-size-6);
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  line-height: 1.3;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: opacity var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__action[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__action[disabled] {
  cursor: not-allowed;
  opacity: 0.5;
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__action:not([disabled]):hover {
    opacity: 0.88;
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__action:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__action--primary {
  background-color: var(--v-accent);
  border-color: var(--v-accent);
  color: var(--v-accent-fg);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__action--ghost {
  background-color: transparent;
  border-color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 35%, transparent);
  color: currentColor;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__icon {
  display: inline-flex;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 1.125rem;
  block-size: 1.125rem;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__icon svg {
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__action {
    transition: none;
  }
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Message / centered card states (consent, photo, processing). A single
   max-width column keeps short forms from stretching edge-to-edge on desktop.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sai-b309s2jg__message {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding-block: var(--sai-size-7);
  text-align: center;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__panel-card {
  inline-size: 100%;
  /* Column width is in em (relative to this snippet's own font-size), not rem:
     many merchant themes set `html { font-size: 62.5% }`, which would collapse a
     rem-based column to ~62% of its intended width and cramp the form. */
  max-inline-size: 30em;
  margin-inline: auto;
  padding-block: var(--sai-size-5);
  /* A consent/photo step is a form, not an editorial gallery — left-aligned
     reads cleanly and keeps the header axis flush with the checkbox list. */
  text-align: start;
}

/* The step's primary action spans the form column; the back link centers below it. */
.sai-b309s2jg__panel-card .sai-b309s2jg__action--primary {
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__panel-card .sai-b309s2jg__link {
  display: block;
  inline-size: fit-content;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__panel-h {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-2);
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  line-height: 1.12;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__panel-p {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-5);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__fine {
  margin: var(--sai-size-4) 0 0;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.55;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__link {
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-3);
  border: none;
  background: none;
  color: var(--v-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 3px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__link:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Consent — one toggle row per scope; the start button enables once all are on. */
.sai-b309s2jg__consent-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-4);
  text-align: start;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__check {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  line-height: 1.45;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__check input[type='checkbox'] {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  inline-size: 1.125rem;
  block-size: 1.125rem;
  margin-block-start: 0.0625rem;
  accent-color: var(--v-accent);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__check-title {
  display: block;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__check-desc {
  display: block;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
}

/* Inline-consent gate on the product list (opt-in mode): the single checkbox
   row plus the full disclosure as fine print, centred above the start button. */
.sai-b309s2jg__consent-gate {
  max-inline-size: 34rem;
  margin: var(--sai-size-5) auto 0;
  text-align: start;
}

/* ── Step 2 — add photo (dropzone / uploading / ready) ─────────────────────
   Centered column shell hosting the three states. */
.sai-b309s2jg__photo {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  inline-size: 100%;
  max-inline-size: 34rem;
  margin-inline: auto;
  text-align: center;
}

/* Drag-and-drop / browse zone (no photo yet). */
.sai-b309s2jg__dropzone {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-6) var(--sai-size-4);
  border: 1.5px dashed var(--v-line);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-lg);
  background-color: var(--v-surface);
  color: var(--v-ink);
  text-align: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1),
    background-color var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}
@media (hover: hover) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__dropzone:hover {
    border-color: var(--v-accent);
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--v-accent) 5%, var(--sai-color-bg));
  }
}
.sai-b309s2jg__dropzone:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__dropzone-icon {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  inline-size: 2.75rem;
  block-size: 2.75rem;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  background-color: var(--v-accent);
  color: var(--v-accent-fg);
}
/* Constrain the glyph so it sits centred in the accent badge with padding —
   without this the unsized SVG fills the whole badge edge-to-edge. */
.sai-b309s2jg__dropzone-icon svg {
  inline-size: 1.5rem;
  block-size: 1.5rem;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__dropzone-title {
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__dropzone-hint {
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}

/* "Take a photo" — camera capture, mobile only. On a precise pointer (desktop)
   the capture attribute is ignored and it would just re-open the picker, so the
   dropzone's "browse" is the desktop path and this is hidden. */
.sai-b309s2jg__photo-actions {
  display: flex;
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-3);
}
@media (hover: hover) and (pointer: fine) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__photo-actions {
    display: none;
  }
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ghostbtn {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-block-size: 2.75rem;
  padding: var(--sai-size-2) var(--sai-size-4);
  border: 1px solid var(--v-line);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--v-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  cursor: pointer;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ghostbtn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ghostbtn-ic {
  inline-size: 1rem;
  block-size: 1rem;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__consent-note {
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-4);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}

/* Uploading card — replaces the dropzone while an upload is in flight. */
.sai-b309s2jg__upload-card {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-4);
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-4) var(--sai-size-5);
  border: 1px solid var(--v-line);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-lg);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  text-align: start;
}
/* Indeterminate spinning ring — fetch() gives no upload progress, so never a %. */
.sai-b309s2jg__uring {
  inline-size: 3rem;
  block-size: 3rem;
  flex: none;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__uring svg {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  animation: sai-b309s2jg-spin 0.85s linear infinite;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__uring-track { stroke: var(--v-line); }
.sai-b309s2jg__uring-arc { stroke: var(--v-accent); }
@keyframes sai-b309s2jg-spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }
.sai-b309s2jg__upload-meta { flex: 1 1 auto; min-inline-size: 0; }
.sai-b309s2jg__upload-title {
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  color: var(--v-ink);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__upload-file {
  margin-block-start: 0.1875rem;
  font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__upload-cancel {
  flex: none;
  align-self: flex-start;
  border: none;
  background: none;
  padding: 0;
  color: var(--v-ink-2);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  cursor: pointer;
}
@media (hover: hover) { .sai-b309s2jg__upload-cancel:hover { color: var(--v-ink); } }
.sai-b309s2jg__upload-cancel:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg); outline-offset: 2px; }

/* Photo-ready card — bordered two-column (thumbnail + status). */
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-card {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--sai-size-4);
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-4);
  border: 1px solid var(--v-line);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-lg);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  text-align: start;
  box-shadow: 0 1px 2px color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 4%, transparent);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-thumb {
  position: relative;
  inline-size: 8.5rem;
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
  flex: none;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-thumb-img {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-label {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-end: 0.5rem;
  inset-inline-start: 0.5rem;
  padding: 0.1875rem 0.4375rem;
  border-radius: 6px;
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-bg) 84%, transparent);
  color: var(--v-ink);
  font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
  font-size: 0.625rem;
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-info {
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-inline-size: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-pill {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.4375rem;
  padding: 0.3125rem 0.6875rem;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: var(--v-success-soft);
  color: var(--v-success);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-dot {
  inline-size: 0.4375rem;
  block-size: 0.4375rem;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: var(--v-success);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-title {
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  color: var(--v-ink);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-note {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 0.78125rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-swap {
  margin-block-start: 0.125rem;
  padding: 0.5625rem 0.9375rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--v-line);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
  color: var(--v-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  cursor: pointer;
}
@media (hover: hover) { .sai-b309s2jg__ready-swap:hover { border-color: var(--v-accent); color: var(--v-accent); } }
.sai-b309s2jg__ready-swap:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg); outline-offset: 2px; }

/* Footer — Back (left) + Continue (right). Continue is full-width on phones. */
.sai-b309s2jg__photo-footer {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
  inline-size: 100%;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-5);
}
.sai-b309s2jg__continue {
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  padding: 0.8125rem 1.625rem;
  background-color: var(--v-accent);
  color: var(--v-accent-fg);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-body-weight-bold);
  cursor: pointer;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 16px color-mix(in srgb, var(--v-accent) 20%, transparent);
  transition: opacity var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}
@media (hover: hover) { .sai-b309s2jg__continue:not([disabled]):hover { opacity: 0.9; } }
.sai-b309s2jg__continue:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg); outline-offset: 2px; }
.sai-b309s2jg__continue[disabled] {
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
  box-shadow: none;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__file-input {
  position: absolute;
  inline-size: 1px;
  block-size: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__notice {
  margin-block-end: var(--sai-size-3);
  padding: var(--sai-size-2) var(--sai-size-3);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__notice--error {
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-fg) 8%, transparent);
  color: var(--v-ink);
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__uring svg {
    animation-duration: 1.6s;
  }
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Looks — the contact sheet. One tile per product; each starts blurred
   ("Developing…") and resolves sharp when its render lands. Reveal is staggered
   by the JS, so tiles sharpen one after another like a darkroom print.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sai-b309s2jg__looks-head {
  margin-block-end: var(--sai-size-5);
  text-align: center;
}

/* Matches the collection grid: fixed two-up on mobile, centered auto-fit from the
   tablet breakpoint up so any look count clusters under the centered heading
   instead of hugging the left with an empty trailing column. */
.sai-b309s2jg__looksgrid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: var(--sai-size-5) var(--sai-size-4);
}

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__looksgrid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 240px));
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--sai-size-6) var(--sai-size-5);
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  background: none;
  color: inherit;
  font-family: inherit;
  text-align: start;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile--dev {
  cursor: default;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile-figure {
  position: relative;
  aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile-img {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  transition: filter 0.9s var(--sai-ease-out-1), opacity 0.9s var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile--dev .sai-b309s2jg__tile-img {
  filter: blur(14px) saturate(0.18);
  opacity: 0.55;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile--done .sai-b309s2jg__tile-img {
  filter: none;
  opacity: 1;
}

/* The "Generating…" / error label, centred over the blurred plate; fades out on done. */
.sai-b309s2jg__tile-dev {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-end: var(--sai-size-3);
  inset-inline: 0;
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 0.625rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.22em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--v-on-stage);
  text-shadow: 0 1px 6px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.45);
  transition: opacity 0.5s var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

/* Pulse the pending label so a slow render reads as active work, not a stall. */
.sai-b309s2jg__tile--dev .sai-b309s2jg__tile-dev {
  animation: sai-b309s2jg-pulse 1.6s var(--sai-ease-out-1) infinite;
}

@keyframes sai-b309s2jg-pulse {
  0%,
  100% {
    opacity: 0.55;
  }
  50% {
    opacity: 1;
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile--done .sai-b309s2jg__tile-dev {
  opacity: 0;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile--error .sai-b309s2jg__tile-img {
  filter: grayscale(1);
  opacity: 0.4;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile--error .sai-b309s2jg__tile-dev {
  color: var(--v-on-stage);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__tile-cap {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.125rem;
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__disclaimer {
  margin: var(--sai-size-6) auto 0;
  max-inline-size: 52ch;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  text-align: center;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}

/* Results-footer notice, only ever shown to surface a server error (mixed-category
   compare) or the minimum-products requirement — emphasised over the muted base. */
.sai-b309s2jg__disclaimer--error {
  color: var(--v-ink);
}

/* One cell of the compare grid, cropped via background geometry. Fills a
   position:relative container (tile figure / spotlight frame / filmstrip thumb);
   the container's aspect-ratio is set to the cell's shape so the square grid crops
   without distortion. */
.sai-b309s2jg__cell,
.sai-b309s2jg__tile-cell,
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb-cell {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
}

/* The filmstrip thumb crops a grid cell too, so it needs its own clip + position
   context (the tile figure and spotlight frame already provide theirs). */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__tile-img,
  .sai-b309s2jg__tile-dev {
    transition: none;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__tile--dev .sai-b309s2jg__tile-dev {
    animation: none;
    opacity: 1;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__tile--dev .sai-b309s2jg__tile-img {
    filter: none;
    opacity: 1;
  }
}

/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Spotlight (mini-PDP). Stacks on mobile (image over controls); two columns on
   desktop (image left, controls right) with the filmstrip spanning the bottom.
   ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.sai-b309s2jg__spotlight {
  display: grid;
  /* minmax(0, …), not a bare 1fr: the generated slide is a square cell whose
     width tracks the frame height (58vh). A bare `1fr` (= minmax(auto, 1fr))
     lets that square's max-content blow the column past the viewport, so the
     whole stacked column overflows on mobile. The 0 min clamps the track to the
     available width (the same guard the two-column layout below already uses). */
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
  gap: var(--sai-size-4);
  max-inline-size: 980px;
  margin-inline: auto;
}

@media (min-width: 850px) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__spotlight {
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(0, 0.95fr);
    grid-template-areas:
      'head head'
      'stage controls'
      'gthumbs controls';
    column-gap: var(--sai-size-6);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-head {
    grid-area: head;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-stage {
    grid-area: stage;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-controls {
    grid-area: controls;
    align-self: start;
  }
  /* Only the gallery-thumbnail strip is a direct grid child; the "Compare with"
     strip is nested inside .sp-controls, so it flows in the right column. */
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-strip {
    grid-area: gthumbs;
  }
  /* Two-column layout: the compare block sits in the controls column and flows
     normally — undo the mobile bottom-pin. */
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-compare {
    position: static;
    padding-block-end: 0;
  }
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--sai-size-3);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-name {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--sai-font-heading);
  font-style: var(--sai-font-heading-style);
  font-weight: var(--sai-font-heading-weight);
  font-size: 1.0625rem;
  line-height: 1.25;
  color: var(--v-ink);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__iconbtn {
  display: inline-flex;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  inline-size: 2.25rem;
  block-size: 2.25rem;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--v-ink);
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__iconbtn .sai-b309s2jg__icon {
  inline-size: 1.375rem;
  block-size: 1.375rem;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__iconbtn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__iconbtn-spacer {
  inline-size: 2.25rem;
}

/* The stage hugs the frame's (variable) width and centers in its column, so the
   nav chevrons — absolutely positioned at the stage's inner edges — stay glued to
   the media edges regardless of how wide the current slide is. */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-stage {
  position: relative;
  inline-size: 100%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  /* Neutral backdrop behind the (width-hugging) media so a portrait slide reads
     as sitting on a plate rather than floating on the page. Theme-derived so it
     re-skins with the storefront palette. */
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
}

/* Fixed height, variable width: every slide sits at the same fixed height and the
   frame hugs the media's natural width — no letterbox, no crop, no distortion. The
   AI try-on and product media alike keep their own aspect at that height. */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-frame {
  position: relative;
  block-size: clamp(340px, 58vh, 540px);
  inline-size: fit-content;
  max-inline-size: 100%;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

/* The try-on cell keeps its own aspect (set inline): fixed to the stage height,
   width derived from the aspect — so it scales with the stage at variable width. */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-cell {
  position: relative;
  block-size: 100%;
  inline-size: auto;
  max-inline-size: 100%;
}

/* Product images / videos: fixed to the stage height, natural (variable) width —
   the frame hugs them so there's no letterbox. Media too wide for the column is
   capped to it and fit per the merchant's object-fit choice. */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-media {
  display: block;
  block-size: 100%;
  inline-size: auto;
  max-inline-size: 100%;
  object-fit: var(--sai-b309s2jg-spotlight-fit, contain);
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-mark {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-end: var(--sai-size-2);
  inset-inline-end: var(--sai-size-3);
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  /* On-photo, not a light letterbox (unlike the VTO experience stage), so the
     mark inks white with a drop-shadow to read over darker try-on imagery. */
  color: var(--v-on-stage);
  text-decoration: none;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-mark svg {
  display: block;
  block-size: 13px;
  inline-size: auto;
  fill: currentColor;
  filter: drop-shadow(0 1px 3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.45));
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-arrow {
  position: absolute;
  inset-block-start: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  inline-size: 2.25rem;
  block-size: 2.25rem;
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-round);
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sai-color-bg) 82%, transparent);
  color: var(--v-ink);
  box-shadow: 0 1px 6px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.12);
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-arrow--prev {
  inset-inline-start: var(--sai-size-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-arrow--next {
  inset-inline-end: var(--sai-size-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-arrow .sai-b309s2jg__icon {
  inline-size: 1.25rem;
  block-size: 1.25rem;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-controls {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__ctl-label {
  margin: var(--sai-size-3) 0 var(--sai-size-2);
  font-size: 0.625rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__chips {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__chip {
  min-block-size: 2.375rem;
  padding: 0 var(--sai-size-3);
  border: 1px solid var(--v-line-2);
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--v-ink);
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color var(--sai-duration-1) var(--sai-ease-out-1);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__chip[aria-pressed='true'] {
  border-color: var(--v-accent);
  background-color: var(--v-accent);
  color: var(--v-accent-fg);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__chip:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--sai-color-fg);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-add {
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-4);
  inline-size: 100%;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-view {
  align-self: center;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-strip {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--sai-size-2);
  overflow-x: auto;
  padding-block: var(--sai-size-1);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb {
  position: relative;
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  inline-size: 3.25rem;
  block-size: 4rem;
  padding: 0;
  border: 1.5px solid transparent;
  border-radius: var(--sai-radius-sm);
  background-color: var(--v-plate);
  overflow: hidden;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb[disabled] {
  cursor: default;
  opacity: 0.5;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb--on {
  border-color: var(--v-accent);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb-img {
  display: block;
  inline-size: 100%;
  block-size: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* Play badge overlaid on a video thumbnail. */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb-play {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: var(--v-on-stage);
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-thumb-play svg {
  inline-size: 1.25rem;
  block-size: 1.25rem;
  filter: drop-shadow(0 1px 3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5));
}

/* "Compare with" — the other products, below the buy controls. Its thumbnail row
   (.sp-strip) scrolls horizontally on its own. On a single-column (narrow)
   viewport it is pinned to the bottom of the screen — see the mobile rule below. */
.sai-b309s2jg__sp-compare {
  margin-block-start: var(--sai-size-4);
  padding-block-start: var(--sai-size-4);
  border-block-start: 1px solid var(--v-line);
}

.sai-b309s2jg__sp-compare-h {
  margin: 0 0 var(--sai-size-2);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--v-ink-3);
}

/* Mobile: pin the compare switcher to the bottom of the viewport so it stays
   reachable while the shopper scrolls the taller spotlight view. It is the last
   block in the flow, so position:sticky has no travel room — a fixed bar is the
   only way to keep it on screen. The buy controls reserve matching bottom space
   so nothing hides behind the bar at rest. The opaque background is load-bearing:
   content scrolls underneath the bar. */
@media (max-width: 849px) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-compare {
    position: fixed;
    inset-inline: 0;
    inset-block-end: 0;
    z-index: 40;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--sai-size-3) var(--sai-size-4);
    background-color: var(--sai-color-bg);
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--v-line);
    box-shadow: 0 -4px 16px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.08);
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__sp-controls {
    padding-block-end: 8rem;
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__chip {
    transition: none;
  }
}

/* Two-column layouts and the compare pin above target ≥850px; add phone tweaks
   for the photo step here. */
@media (max-width: 849px) {
  .sai-b309s2jg__photo-footer {
    flex-direction: column-reverse;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__continue {
    inline-size: 100%;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__photo-footer .sai-b309s2jg__link {
    align-self: center;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__ready-card {
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  /* Mobile: show the whole uploaded photo — full width and full natural height,
     uncropped. The desktop thumb crops to a fixed 4/5 box; on mobile we let the
     image set its own height so the full-body shot is shown in full. */
  .sai-b309s2jg__ready-thumb {
    inline-size: 100%;
    block-size: auto;
    aspect-ratio: auto;
  }
  .sai-b309s2jg__ready-thumb-img {
    block-size: auto;
    object-fit: contain;
  }
}
{% endstylesheet %}

{%- assign content = variant.content -%}
{%- assign cta_text = content.cta_text | default: 'Try these on' -%}

{%- comment -%}
  show_branding defaults to true. Liquid's `| default:` filter would replace an
  explicit `false`, so use an explicit nil check.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if content.show_branding == nil -%}
  {%- assign show_branding = true -%}
{%- else -%}
  {%- assign show_branding = content.show_branding -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Spotlight media fit — mirrors the platform PDP-gallery `spotlight_object_fit`
  control (see the ty137c1l / im4x2uig gallery snippets). Only 'cover' and
  'contain' are valid CSS object-fit values here; default to the production-safe
  'contain' on anything else.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign spotlight_fit = content.spotlight_object_fit -%}
{%- if spotlight_fit != 'cover' and spotlight_fit != 'contain' -%}
  {%- assign spotlight_fit = 'contain' -%}
{%- endif -%}

